Central European Media Falls Most Since 2009 on Global Slowdown

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-05T14:41:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/central-european-media-falls-most-since-2009-on-global-slowdown.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV)  tumbled the most in 2 1/2 years in Czech trading as
investors ditched riskier assets worldwide on concern the global
economic recovery is stalling.  The broadcaster known as CME fell as much as 19 percent,
its biggest drop since January 2009, and traded down 11 percent
to 253 koruna by 4:28 p.m. in Prague. In  New York , its home
market, the stock last traded down 7 percent to $14.80.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  